I don't understand the process for Rules hearings. I don't see Rules in the list of committees of either chamber - so I guess I'm needing to learn more basics. Anyway, thank you for all your advocacy on these issues.

If they are still in play, 1548 Rail Workers fair and safe leave contracts and 1839 regulating train length are very important for worker/operator safety, and public safety, and 5494 providing shortline rail freight incentives will help farmers in Southeast WA.

Please watch for opportunities to weigh in on other rail improvement possibilities for the state as the Transportation committees deal with the transportation budget near the end of session. We have amendments proposed and a couple of provisos - one for rail yard electrification and one for a state rail education and training curriculum. lcw@climaterailalliance.org
